HEADWORD: Outr
<hw>Ou`tr⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., p.p.
of <ets>outer</ets> to exaggerate, fr. L. <ets>ultra</ets> beyond. See
<er>Outrage</er>.]</ety> <def>Out of the common course or limits;
extravagant{2}; bizarre; outlandish{2}; <as>as, an <ex>outr⟦eacute⟧</ex>
costume</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>My first mental development had in it much of the uncommon -- even
much of the <qex>outr⟦eacute⟧</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>E. A.
Poe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outreach</ent>⟦br⟧
